Description: Thin and long copper alloy rod of circular cross-section, heavily corroded and broken into five fragments, maybe a kohl- stick or stem of a dipper (?)
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, Possibly "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 19
Curator's comments: Maybe the "stem of a dipper" found in chamber 19, mentioned by W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 77 § 76 ?
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 61 § 57) (?)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.46, p.77, pl. 27, p.185, pl.27)
